Reference

Reading datasets

Functions for loading datasets used in a FASTGenomics analysis.

ds_info()

Get information on all available datasets in this analysis.

load_data()

Loads a single dataset to a Seurat object.

Available default readers

Description of the default readers.

read_anndata_to_seurat()

Read AnnData to Seurat with Seurat's function ReadH5AD. Please note that this might not work as expected. For your convenience we implemented importing with SeuratDisk for h5ad files from Anndata>=0.7.3. Alternatively, you can use our experimental reader by setting "experimental_readers=TRUE" in load_data.

read_densemat_to_seurat()

Read dense matrix here we need to unpack the dataset before reading it

read_loom_to_seurat()

Reading a loom dataset in Seurat v3 uses loomR and may not work as expected. For your convenience we implemented experimental readers that you can use by setting "experimental_readers=TRUE" in load_data.

read_densecsv_to_seurat()

Read dense matrix in csv form

read_densetsv_to_seurat()

Read dense matrix in tsv form

read_seurat_to_seurat()

Read a Seurat object.

read_10xhdf5_to_seurat()

Read 10x hdf5 dataset into seurat.

read_10xmtx_to_seurat()

Read 10x mtx (mex) dataset to seurat.
